SIMPLE: reprehension
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reprehension
<hw>Rep`re*hen"sion</hw> <pr>(-sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>reprehensio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧pr⟦eacute⟧hension</ets>.]</ety> <def>Reproof; censure;
blame; disapproval.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This Basilius took as though his mistress had given him a secret
<qex>reprehension</qex> that he had not showed more gratefulness to
Dorus.</q> <rj><qau>Sir P. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Censure; reproof; reprimand. See
<er>Admonition</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reprehensive</ent>⟦br⟧
